ign=left class=m><span class=title> Spankda Updage -- Level 45</span><hr size=1> I'm a quad-kiting maniac.  The xp is tremendous.  I'm half-way through 45.<br>
<br>
Here's some notes for solo and multi-kiting:<br>
<br>
1.  Drakkel Dire Wolves in GD are now green and no longer worth my time or energy.  They are the easiest quad-kite going before level 45.<br>
<br>
2.  Ferocious Kodiaks in GD are now green, but Savage and above Kodiaks are still blue.  Hardly anyone bothers to camp the Kodiak caves and getting four can be fairly easy if you run into the cave and agro them.<br>
<br>
The Kodiak caves are near the Velk entrance.  From the dragon circle, run out the archway straight.  You'll find Kodiaks.<br>
<br>
3.  Elder Shardwurms in GD are solo-able.  I haven't tried an Ancient at 45, but at 44 I could not solo an Ancient.<br>
<br>
4.  The Coldain huts in EW just South of Kael Drakkel has Icefang the dire wolf and some ghostly Coldain (only at night).  Around these huts are tons and tons of walruses. <br>
<br>
The walruses are very easy to quad-kite with lots of open spaces around the huts to run.  They were mostly blue to me at 44 and a lot of xp.  Terrible loot.  <br>
<br>
Killing walruses will spawn the Ulthork Man-o-War at this site.  I could not solo a Man-o-War at 44 unless I got extremely lucky.  They resist a lot and have a ton of HP.<br>
<br>
5.  Ulthorks North of the bridge in EW are excellent xp and loot.  In fact, I find myself going back here all the time simply because the loot is so good.  I probably make 20pp or more on items and cash from each set of four Ulthorks I quad.<br>
<br>
Ulthork Hunters are now all green at 45.  About two-thirds of these green Hunters still give me xp, though.  The Warriors are all blue.<br>
<br>
Hunters and Warriors each drop Ulthork Tusks at about the same rate.  For every four tusks you can go to Chief Kalan in CS and turn them into him for a gem or item.  So far, I've gotten a Blue Diamond, Diamond, two Sapphire Necklaces (worth 132pp at vendor), a Jacinth, and a Black Sapphire.<br>
<br>
I'm hooked on the tusks.<br>
<br>
The Wooley Rhinos and Walruses in this area are tied to the Ulthork spawn.  If there are no Ulthorks, kill the Rhinos and Walruses.<br>
<br>
The Rhinos are blue and have a ton of HP.  I could solo one at 40, but it took all my mana.  At 45, I can multi-kite only two Rhinos.  <br>
<br>
Rhinos are *not* on any faction, so when they get to the critical health level, they stop following me in a group.  As a result, you must solo finish the Rhinos.  I must cast Harvest to kill both.<br>
<br>
6.  Wyverns in CS are terrific.  If you attack one and another is nearby, it will agro on you.  Wyverns have a bit over 3000 hp, so you won't be able to multi-kite them.  <br>
<br>
I've found pulling them down to the beach is the best bet for avoiding the drakes.  However, some of the Wyverns will gate back to their spawn point.  You will have to run up the cliffs and back to the Wyvern's spawn point to finish it off. <br>
<br>
I've found the Wyverns to be very heavily camped at times.  I've only killed about 10 or so and have gotten only one gem and that was vendor trash worth 37pp.  Wyvernd do drop cash and other items.<br>
<br>
If I get two Wyverns, I'll snare both, nuke one to death by kiting both, then run to the Wyvern tower and zone into Skyshrine to clear agro.  You must be Dubious+ with CoV to use this technique.<br>
<br>
I'm primarily hunting Ulthorks now because I'm hoping for another blue diamond from the tusks.  Some pulls I'll get two tusks.  Other times, I'll kill 20 Ulthorks with no tusks.  At 45, I could potentially quad Warriors and have a bubble of mana left -- IF I could find four Warriors (which I normally can not). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utegellan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tegellan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/9/01 3:33:05 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spankda Updage -- Level 45</span><hr size=1>  Hehe gotta love your updates, they have a ton of good info for lower level wizards, that way i can always seem like the helpful knowing wizards when the lower level wizards I know ask me for good places to hunt <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
